title: For Sale:  Reminton Model 8
location: Cottage Grove, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent: REMINGTON MODEL 8 SEMI-AUTOMATIC for sale.  This particular version is chambered in the potent .35 Reminton cartridge.  It is is perfect operational condition and has been a great addition to our gun collection ( I actually had a problem with my go to deer rifle this last season and took this out of retirement and harvested two nice does in wisconsin and a beautiful 14-Point bruiser here in MN at 202 yards with this rifle!!!)  It is a blowback operated rifle, much like the operation of modern semi-automatic handguns.  It is a beautiful piece of hardware that would look great in anyones collection, or to be totally honest would and does make an excellent hunting rifle. Lets be honest here, there are a few knocks and dings in the rifle .  It was used prior to me making this post so lets all be adults here and realize its not brand new out of the box, but it is in damn good condition considering some of the others that are left out there.  Some people have commented on the forend having a gouge out of it.  The rifle took a spill about 40 years ago on a stump and a piece was broken off.  As I got older I took it upon myself to fix it and ended uniformly sanding the sides to mtch. In no way does this hinder the performance of the rifle.  If its really a big deal, I know a man personally who has the jigs to make a new one or there are replacements on the internet. I would rate the overall condition of this rifle at 95 % and have had a few people look at it and people that have seen me shoot it at the farm offer a considerable amount of money for it.  It also comes with 5 rounds of ammunition on an origional stripper clip ( I know what these go for and its right around 75-100$ a piece).I know what these rifles go for and what it is worth, so please dont waste your time or mine with a low ball offer.  The only trade that I would even consider is for an M1-Garand, 1917 enfield, 1903 springfield,  of course cash would be thrown in on my end......, or unless you have a sweet package deal of a few guns, seeing as I'm a Milsurp collecter and i might just need what you have CASH ONLY gets you....-The Rifle of course-The ammunition-The origional stripper clipp made for and the rifle itself-Soft sided transport caseLike I said lowballs will be ignored, but if you ave a reasonable one, throw it my way, you never know unless you ask.  I will also not sell to anyone unless you have a PTP, C/C or a C&R license.  I know you dont need one, but with all this shit going on in the world thats the last thing I need on my plate.CASH/TRADE ONLY LOCAL SALES ONLY. To release the bolt, either pull it back slightly or use the bolt release button. Magazines go in and out of the Vepr enlarged magazine well very easily, and do not require “rocking” them in as on the Saiga. Empty magazines drop free of the gun when released. Another example of this is the spring loaded pin on top of the dust cover latch which must be depressed in order to push the button in and lift up the top cover. This prevents the hinged dust cover from ever coming open if the gun is dropped, or during recoil. The all important bolt of the shotgun is precisely machined steel- not a cast component as on other AK platform guns. The Vepr comes with a Picatinny rail attached on the top of the dust cover for those wanting to use magnified or red-dot optics. If not, the Vepr 12 has the most easily adjustable rear sight of any shotgun. It offers tool-less repeatable adjustments for both elevation AND windage. A 19” chrome lined externally threaded barrel (same thread as Saiga) with muzzle cap completes the gun, and allows easy attachment of flash hiders, muzzles brakes, chokes, and sound suppressors.
